The Bayelsa State Governorship Election Petitions Tribunal sitting in Abuja, has reserved judgment in a petition filed by the candidate of the Liberation Movement (LM), Mr.Vijah Opuama, challenging the eligibility of the deputy governor, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, in the last November gubernatorial election. The deputy governor on his part told the tribunal that he cannot be sued due to the fact that the law does not allow him to institute a legal action in an electoral dispute. Ewhrudjakpo is the 4th respondent in the petition filed by the candidate of the Liberation Movement (LM) in the  November 16, 2019, governorship election in Bayelsa Sate. Vijah Opuama is challenging Ewhrudjakpo’s qualification to stand in the nelection. Opuama alleged that there were discrepancies in the name of the deputy governor on his National Youth Service Corps (NYSC’s) exemption certificate.